comment:
* Information about how to respond to an incoming call. Call screening apps can construct an
     * instance of this class using {@link CallResponse.Builder}.

variables.name: CALL_COMPOSER_ATTACHMENT_PICTURE
variables.comment:
* Bit flag indicating whether to show the picture attachment for call composer.
         *
         * Used with {@link Builder#setCallComposerAttachmentsToShow(int)}.

variables.name: CALL_COMPOSER_ATTACHMENT_LOCATION
variables.comment:
* Bit flag indicating whether to show the location attachment for call composer.
         *
         * Used with {@link Builder#setCallComposerAttachmentsToShow(int)}.

variables.name: CALL_COMPOSER_ATTACHMENT_SUBJECT
variables.comment:
* Bit flag indicating whether to show the subject attachment for call composer.
         *
         * Used with {@link Builder#setCallComposerAttachmentsToShow(int)}.

variables.name: CALL_COMPOSER_ATTACHMENT_PRIORITY
variables.comment:
* Bit flag indicating whether to show the priority attachment for call composer.
         *
         * Used with {@link Builder#setCallComposerAttachmentsToShow(int)}.

methods.name: public boolean getDisallowCall()
methods.comment: * @return Whether the incoming call should be blocked.

methods.name: public boolean getRejectCall()
methods.comment:
* @return Whether the incoming call should be disconnected as if the user had manually
         * rejected it.

methods.name: public boolean getSilenceCall()
methods.comment: * @return Whether the ringtone should be silenced for the incoming call.

methods.name: public boolean getSkipCallLog()
methods.comment: * @return Whether the incoming call should not be displayed in the call log.

methods.name: public boolean getSkipNotification()
methods.comment: * @return Whether a missed call notification should not be shown for the incoming call.

methods.name: public boolean getShouldScreenCallViaAudioProcessing()
methods.comment:
* @return Whether we should enter the {@link Call#STATE_AUDIO_PROCESSING} state to allow
         * for further screening of the call.
         * @hide

methods.name: public int getCallComposerAttachmentsToShow()
methods.comment: * @return A bitmask of call composer attachments that should be shown to the user.
